Package graph

Interface Edge

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Link
    public interface Edge
    Whether a graph is implemented using an adjacency matrix or a adjacency list, edges are an essential element of a graph as these establish the connection between two nodes.

    An edge, at its simplest implementation, consists on a start vertex and a finish vertex and the weight of the connection between these. Notice that the start vertex and a finish vertex encode the direction of the edge.

    The Edge interface provides methods for getting and setting the two vertices and the weight of the connection between them.
